values:
There's a huge party May 2nd.
I'm working all summer at a Law Firm and at a Scuba Shop.
My new tigercard picture looks like I have horns made from hair (damned hats).
We have a house on N. College Street (kick ass).
My exams will soon be over (thank god).
I'm dating someone (as confusing as it may be).
and otherwise life is good... had to be cheerful after my shitty depressing last post.

Yes as my title says it is all so true.  This is the time where I reflect back on the year.  I reflect back on the friends and I have made some great ones which I will truly miss this summer.  Made two great friends who have many similar interests and will be my roomates next year: Russel and Henry.  Definitely will miss the wild nights at George's with Pantelis, Birdsong, Clay, and others.

That allowed for a wonderful first semester.  But second semester allowed for different plans... she really was unexpected and yet when I met her, I couldn't help but feel attracted.  And then, it felt as if I'd known her for years.  Slowly we got to know each other more... and I fell in love.  Unfortunately so did she.  Only then did I realize she had a boyfriend.  And now we've been seeing each other for several months and those months of frustration are finally setting in.  She makes me smile in a way no one else can and when I'm with her, I know everything is great... but... little things that shouldn't bother me are starting to.  Its the pent up frustration seeking a vent.  We're not officially together and how could we be.  She still can't decide who she wants and I'm walking along thinking she'll pick me.  Me? a 20 year old Junior who isn't even sure he'll get into law school.

I know this summer will be rough and I want to spend time with her but... I can't. I won't spend time with her if it means us arguing.  I don't know if its me speaking in blindness caused by love or what in the hell is going on but...just frustration.  I guess it's because we're not together in public and I want to be.  We can't even tell her damned roomate... and yet, she acts as if we're normal friends in public... how does she do it? how does she handle it?!

In the first semester, I search for love.  In the second, I quit searching and let life continue and it found me.  Yet once more I feel that everything I've desired has fallen into my lap and I don't know how to handle it.  And so to this hapless void I commit this entry, a lone thought, a frustration from the recesses of my mind only to be lost in cyberspace.

To hell with my thoughts, for now, I must focus on the present and ignore all other things.

Looking back on it all, I can see all my mistakes.
I can see all the missed opportunities,
and all my stupid outakes.
I can see all my messed up friendships,
and all that I did wrong,
but most of all, I can see who I was.

But that was then, and this is now,
yet, I can't help but think:
"It's funny you know,
I thought I knew who I was back then,
a senior about to graduate,
the king of the hill,
I thought I had life figured out,
Boy had I thought wrong."

Life's little stumbles,
those little falls,
the ones I thought were the world,
and the ones I worried the most about.
Did they matter any?
Now I can tell you not.
For today I am still fine,
and some of those problems still aren't worked out.

Now every day I learn something new,
and yet the more I learn, the more I realize I don't know.
But it's cool you know,
my friends teach me about life each day,
lessons that I couldn't learn any other way.

And so now before time's end,
I can't help but wonder who I was then,
Why does it seem another lifetime,
yet when all that's happened is less than 2 year's blend.
I am happy with who I am now,
Happy with what I have,
I know I still make mistakes,
but that's me, that's who I am,
I know I'm not perfect.
And so now I thank my friends,
for without them, I would not be,
the good, the bad, it's all parts of who I choose to be.
Between Thursday and Saturday nights, this has definitely been one heck of a weekend! The End.

you know looking back on it, today was an awesome day.  Only had 1 class, played a bit of poker, hung out with friends, and had lunch with Kelly.  She's a pretty cool girl and it was a good time just sitting down and talking about anything and everything for a couple hours.

and as usual, it's FRICKING FREEZING IN HERE!  so I'm gonna wrap myself in my blanket and go to sleep now.

well, this morning, the English department head walks into our class.  Waits for us to settle down for a minute or two, and then starts with: I'm sorry to announce that Dr. Bancroft passed away this morning of a heart attack... so our whole class is sitting there going WTF?!  I was dumbfounded.  Well, he pretty much said class is cancelled till they can get someone to take care of it, most likely a GTA and so to expect an email.... talk about odd, especially since we'd just finished talking about The Inferno (Dante).

I find it sad that the knowledge he had was lost and he was definitely a bright man and an alright professor.

So apparently I'm a decent poker player... I took 1st place in the last 2 of 4 tournaments and made it to the final table 3 out of 4 times.  Thus far my winnings include a 5 CD Changer Stereo and a set of 200 chips.  Not too shabby IMO for free buy-in tourneys.  

Now for Halloween.  This started thursday night with Heather's birthday.   Friday, Halloween Party with Rocky.  That boy is funny and his friend from UA is definitely a 9 on my scale, especially in that angel outfit (though she still needed horns).  Saturday, block party at Heather's and seeing Jason Barts in drag talking to the cop for 20 minutes was classic, plus Catie as my sexy secretary definitely made my night.  Sunday, out for coffee with a couple friends, hung out, that's about it.

This week is flying by! Bush got elected (ALRIGHT!) and now it's already Thursday! and work is in 6 hours, Sleep Time!

P.S. oh yeah, I definitely lost the Flower's Avenue house due to previous offers... so back in the search of a house.
It's amusing how fast news spreads through this little town! Oh well, no big deal.  People talk, it's what we do... hopefully no misconstrued notions come out of this...

That's all that can be said about that one.  Had a good time at Benji's friday night and an even better time at Clay's saturday night.

English papers suck hardcore.
was the birth of Commoner's Production Inc.  if you want to see the video I edited drop me an IM and you can find our idiotic stuntman doing what he does best... stunts.

great ending to an awesome weekend... minus the no spotlighting.  Ahh well, at least I got to hang with some friends, get some gear worked out for the bike, and finish my work weekend this month.  and now back to planning next weekend and possible stupid stuff ;)

luck is something you make, not something you have.  And by george, I'm going to change my luck with 'em!  Plus it's not like there's nothing I can do about it.  I can change it.  Now I've just got to set my goals and go for em.

Oh yeah, also got my absentee ballot today and voted for the one, the only, the W.  And I also voted for a lot of other republicans b/c I had no idea who they were and were running for the same party I was interested in... coat tail effect.  Also voted for the amendment to the constitution which says parents of minors have to be notified if their kid plans to have an abortion.  Definitely think my views tend to be conservative and not liberal, but I could be middle of the road, who knows.

Today was on HUGE BLAST! I have not played paintball in forever and never speedball.  Today I spent from noon to 5 on the field, shooting people, getting shot at, etc... and WOW!  I'm sore as heck, I'm gonna have a bruise on my left arm and leg (thanks J... though they were good shots) and my left testicle barely got missed but man that was amazing fun!

On top of that I went to a party at Clay's then we meandered over to Kelly's last night.  A girl from AZD (whatever it could be ADZ, no idea) was there and she had drank a bit too much so I drove some stranger's car back to the dorms for her and dropped her off... but better me drive than she drive, I can handle a couple drinks, apparently she could not.  Now if only her sorority sister would quit sending mixed signals... oh well, plenty of fish in the sea, if 1 is missed, try try again.  Peace y'all.

I really hope this involved a LOT of alcohol.
http://uploads.offtopic.com/files/hpa_b.jpg

Weird week.  Had a bad bad week.  Midterm in Financial Account wednesday (got a 92% woot!) and then a midterm in World Lit on Friday and a paper in Micro-Econ due on Friday.  On top of Course registration for friday, having to have door decos up, bulletin board reworked, pool tournament, and food poisoning.  And my plans for tonight got shot to hell.  So hopefully tomorrow night will work or else I may just give up on that issue completely.  Oh well, whatever, eventually it'll all click into place and everything will be alright.

Was gonna edit, but then stupid stuff shouldn't have evidence.
Yay! not sick anymore! now alls I've got to worry about is my micro-econ paper, my financial accounting midterm, my english midterm, and registering for classes.

Motorcycle is coming along slowly but surely.  Trying to do a couple things right now and I think they may work... not too sure if what I'm doing tomorrow is the best idea but as long as it works, that's the matter.  Micro-econ homework is getting tedious and with 2 exams and a paper this week, life is gonna be rough.  Florida was a lot of fun and Anthony is a BIG baby.  Plus I got a couple presents from Patrice so whichever date i cook for next will have a good meal.  Gotta love being french, nothing like a good bottle of wine, a bit of bread, and a bit of brie.

Damn good! Chris Pentelis' 25th birthday and we celebrated.  Friday night was time for George's place.  Little Ben gave me a ride to and from there (thank you man!).  Hung out over there, played a couple games, chilled, then somehow 2:30 AM crept up on us and we were like, hm... and on her way out, got a big hug from mary and then I was like time for sleep. And sleep I did.  Then around noonish I woke up, goofed around for a couple hours and then headed off to work till midnight.  Midnight, I got changed and headed to Clay's for another birthday party (for Chris) and was definitely glad to see Mary.  So around 2:30 AM (I see a pattern here) we all decided we should go on the roof and relax up there.  Mind you I've not drank but there's about 3 tipsy guys and 2 drunk ones and a girl (Mary) climbing a 30 foot makeshift ladder (actually a wall) to the roof, so we got up there and talked for a bit.  Around 3:30 we all came down and I took Mary back to her dorm.  Came back to hear that Mike... retard that he is... driving George's car at the time, got pulled over near Kinnucans.  Mike is 20, the car smelled like a brewery and so did he, and the guy got off with a TICKET!  Lucky lucky lucky.  So anyhow, it's rolling near 4:10 now and we decide it's time for Waffle House.  So quick trip to the ATM, bit of deciding which Waffle House and about 4:45 we make it there.  So Jay, Chris, Clay and I ate breakfast, I dropped Clay off at his place and then once again, it was time for sleep.  And talk about feeling lonely, what I wouldn't have given to come back to my room with a girl to just crawl in bed with and hold and just fall asleep next to.  Strangely enough, I had a dream that I was sleeping next to a gorgeous girl with the sweetest smelling hair with my arms wrapped around her ... and I woke up to find my pillow with my arm wrapped around it... damned dreams ;)

Alright, so now to the serious part of this post.  I've known half these people for what... a couple months and yet it feels that I've known them forever.  I trust Pentelis with my life, Clay is a good man and someone I trust.  Benji definitely is the friend I've thought him to be.  Berford is laid back, and Lucas is a trip, this guy always smiles and always cracks jokes.  George is easy going about everything and throws some good parties.  And right now i'm forgetting a lot of names but 2 weekends from now (b/c next weekend I'm in Florida!), I'll remember them.  Funny how I was looking for brotherhood and now I find some great friends.  Definitely going to be hard to decide whether or not to stay in Auburn
you know what, screw it, if it isn't on my floor, from now on, I'm not handling it.  Tired of having to screw with some friendships b/c of stupid shit like that.

There are thoughts inside my head that I want to spit out, to get out, and yet, I can't.

Alright back to being semi-normal, I don't know what's up... I'm slightly peeved at myself for Clay's party, and then tonight's RA meeting, and etc...  It's a compilation of a lot of little things just slowly dragging me down.  Oh well.

Yeppers... Wednesday was a good night.  Went to George's, had fun, got Mary's # but I think she was drunk so I don't know whether to use it or not.  And I was too stupid to call Erin (and forgot today was friday) so no idea what she's up to for the game tomorrow.  So in hopes of finding a party, I checked with Thomas/Audrey, Dave, and Benji and found zilch.  So yep... after 44 hours awake, I am going to sleep.

Once again... here we are... Sitting at the desk.  Work is over in an hour and a half and alls I can think is yippie! but women are confusing as heck and I can't figure out which 1 to go for.  Hopefully Ivan will cure that.  But since I got her # today, I should try her first... who knows... ARRRRRRGGGGGHHHH, I'm confused.
... WHAT THE FUCK?!  And wooden doors are bad for the health of my hands.  That is all.

So yep, Sociology is definitely my favorite class.  Then again, it's also interesting b/c I hit it off rather well with Erin, but she goes home a lot on weekends so that makes setting up a time where she can come hang out at a party with myself and some friends rather difficult, oh well, its not like I don't have all the time in the world.

Then there's a cute girl that I keep catching staring my way... so first I thought ok there's something on my face, no...  So she kept at it and every time I'd catch her, she'd blush and quickly look away.  On her way out, I got a big smile from her, interesting.  I remember meeting her at some Honor's thing but her name completely skipped my mind.

Then there's Lori whom I'm trying to help out with her guy problems.  Yeah like that's really working.  At least I spent 2 hours massaging she and Tara tonight.  Definitely was enjoyable though.

So yep, apart from taking Chris to the doctor's and hanging out with him a little bit today, the rest of my day was spent in the sea of estrogen.  Must say though, a fair share of them were cute.  I wonder if I can get the cute girl from my sociology class' number... or Erin's... hmm... oh well, we'll see later.

Is Frances the name of a guy or girl? Either way it doesn't matter b/c it's a Hurricane...  But I wonder, why do they give wussy names to hurricanes? I mean come on!  If there was a kid names Frances... the kid would be picked on all the time!

So I've been trying to be nicer to the girls, especially Shannon... not too sure if that's working, especially last night when she went off on me about being such a hypocrite.  Guess she didn't see the part where I was fed up with having to take care of drunk people...  but, ya know, it's not always easy to see someone else's point of view, especially when you REACT to something, I know I'm guilty of that.

So, overall, I've been trying to change my perspective on things... I'm trying to find the good in all situations.  It's so easy to see the bad, to complain, and etc... but I'm pretty sure it doesn't make me a fun person to be around.  Unfortunately, change is slow and progressive...  I wish I could just snap my finger and change would happen.  Ahh well guess I'll just have to keep trying, and if I screw up, get back up and try again.

On a positive note, I saw Benji today, haven't seen him in about a week.  Boy's been busy apparently!  I think I'll talk to him about getting some beer, sit down, hang out this weekend.  Who knows, gotta check how much accounts are doing before I do that.  All in all, things are good, bike's in the process of getting fixed.

Oh yeah, Willie's Wings and Stuff have decent wings but Wingzone = so much better.  Maybe the left-overs from Chilis that Mikie gave me (Mikie kicks ass mind you) could be why I didn't like em, I dunno.  Anyhow, time for sleep.

With her being upset about the frat stuff, yesterday afternoon she gets a call from South Carolina State Trooper to drive up there to ID a body which they found a wallet with belonging to Betty Hodges... so my mom went apeshit, and I understand, I mean she gets a call telling her her best friend is dead... so yep, frat stuff is on hold right now, but I had a good time at the TKE party last, met some girls, don't remember their names, oh well.  Hoping to go out tonight, but I need to get sleep this afternoon 1st ;)

So I talked to my dad and apparently my mom started crying when she found out I wanted to join a fraternity... what the heck is up with that?  someone explain it to me how horribly wrong it is to join a bunch of great guys who are good friends, are fun to be around, and people I fit in with.  Not like I don't spend a ton of time at the TKE house anyhow.  But yeah... so everyone's been asking me how Thomas is doing and then thomas is like thank you for saving my life... just drop it already!  Jeebus!  Oh well, I feel bad for Dave having to drive last night with the party and etc... Then again, poor Chris... She didn't even remember him and completely ignored him when he was in Thomas' room!  Oh well.  Unfortunately, this is pointless ramblings due to lack of sleep... 6 hours in three nights.  That's definitely not enough.  Time for micro-econ HW, later!

So tonight I went to a TKE party just to spend time with the brothers and got to meet a couple girls, Diana being one from Jax that went to BK and a pretty cool girl at that... however, that's not the point of this story.  No, the point is that Thomas and Daniel were GONE and when I mean gone, I mean I got Thomas up to his room, came back 30 mins later to find him in his boxers, passed out in a pool of his own puke, face up with some weird stuff in his mouth.  My first thoughts, OH GOD! he's choked on his own puke and died.  So I go for a pulse, no pulse.  So I pushed on his chest, he spits up some weird shit and then does a shallow breath.  Whew! He's alive!  So I sat him up... eventually dragged him into his bed, my arms now have vomit on them. He gets on his back and I roll him to his stomach with his head off his bed.  By now, a dude comes up and says Daniel is having dry heaves down in the lobby... SON OF A!!!!! Will this night ever end?  So I haul it downstairs, call Mikie and have him help me get Daniel up to his room where we put him in the bath tub.  He puked, said he'd be fine and I cleaned myself off and left... 

Thank god Mikie and Kyle were there, they RULED.  They were helpin me out the whole time and did most the work.  Mikie rocks, I owe him a drink or 3 one of these days.  And no more driving to parties for me.  Let the pledges take people home.

Oh yeah... so about 2 AM I get a call from Dave and I decide to go check on Thomas... well I find Corey in there and the paramedics are on their way to take him to EAMC... so I followed with and stayed with him all night long, talked to his distressed mother, and greeted his dad around 4 AM when he drove out here...  His parents were happy that I stayed with him all night long and he deserved it, he's a good guy.  He's all better now so ... I get to go to sleep, but I spent from 2 AM to 7 AM in the ER  staring at a passed out Thomas.  Thank god he's fine.

So I'm debating pledging TKE...  I wonder how that's gonna go...  Need to spend some time discussing it with the parentals though.  Ahh well, it'll be a fun day tomorrow.  Also need to check on that "make up" thingie, and do my storage unit stuff too... guess that's my TO DO list for tomorrow.  Sleep time so I can wake up early enough to actually do it.
I'm hoping the bridges aren't burned down.  I have an idea about something which may help a little bit the situation... I'll have to look into it.

except screwing up that is, I'm really good at that... and I scattered it on a couple innocent bystanders when it was really just a minor thing that I let grow too much.  I was the monkey throwing shit at the fan.  One of those times when you knew what you did would cause hell...  I'm not the person I want to be, but I'm hoping that i'll be there soon.
This entry was wrong and should have never been made in the first place.

Yeah, it was definitely interesting, actually I was thinking of them (her precisely) right before the party last night.  Here's a quote from her e-mail: " By the way, you appeared (suspiciously) in many of our conference photos. Some of us believe you may be a communist spy..." LoL! Me? communist? HA!  Oh well.  But I had fun at the parties last night, and definitely made a dork of myself but it's ok.  I'm fine with that.  I got the no I was looking for, so that's good, rectifies that :) NEXT! LoL, I love how Auburn has plenty of fish for such a little pond.  Anyhow, time to do homework... I still claim that micro-econ and financial accounting are the devil.

P.S. someone accidentally set fire to one of the elevators in the Commons... great geniuses we have.
I'm about to head out to a party to be gone... and I'm most likely going to take up Tom on his idea... which, I don't think is a good one but whatever.  It's go time.

And I figured out that the thing in which I believe the least is what I want the most.  

That's for another post though... one where I'll discuss love, how it is developped, and it's implications/repurcussions.  The end, sleep time.

Ya know, it's been about 3 weekends that I've gone out on the town here in Auburn and have gone drinking.  All around me my friends have been plastered (minus our DD who was so kind) and I have sat there drinking away not going anywhere.  And so, I wondered to myself, why?

Of course, there's no simple explanation... but IMO, it's done for confidence.  Ya see, tonight at the TKE party, I had a couple drinks and was yet to feel anything... however, the people that were drunk had no problems making fools of themselves dancing in front of everyone.  The alcohol gives you a confidence to do things you could not normally do.

Now that may seem a little far fetched... alright, take this example.  A friend of mine and I were at this party.  Both of us are checking out an obviously hot, and amazingly single girl.  So he looks at me and goes go introduce yourself.  Anyone that's known me more than 5 minutes know that I have nowhere near the balls to go to that (at least without having drank a fair amount).  Well, I retorted that he should do so.  Having had twice as much to drink as I had, he preceded to do so and ended up dancing with her. Lucky bastard.

Now, these two examples prove that alcohol and drunken-ness can be fun.  Don't get me wrong, I don't 100% condone it and yes it is a sin... however, a sin is a sin, whether it be drunk or a lie or stealing a pencil.  Yet, now, I understand why some of the people in this building go out for the intent of getting drunk.  And hopefully, tomorrow night, I shall be too.


And on a parting note... why am I trying to hook Ben and Shannon up together?  I feel like I'm shooting myself in the foot by doing that... not that I had a chance with her in the first place... Gah! confusing.

Good News - My ankle is feeling slightly better.
Bad News - It's my whole lower left leg hurting.

And my shoulders are sore as nuts but I expected it.  A good massage would be nice (hint hint to any girls reading ;) ).  So my event of the day was either the guy in his green speedos running down the hall and back OR the talk with Jackie... not too sure but I'll go with the latter. Ok you're going to say why then did you go ride?  Well, my answer is this, things happen for a reason.  I will not be scared into NOT doing things even if my personal health or safety may be violated.  I knew it on monday that I was going to wreck on tuesday.  I joked about it then and went to sleep with that eerie, hmm I am going to crash feeling.  I woke up quite cheerfully and before I went to ride, I checked my gear with that feeling still there.  In fact, I knew I was going to crash out by the lake and thus came back to the Commons to get my cell phone "just in case."  Well, as it turns out, there was no reception where I wrecked and there was no way around it other than not take that road.

Anyhow, I lost my train of thought b/c I spent the last 2 hours talking with Shannon and Sarah... so sleepy time.

And I got neither.  I pretty much did a highside crash after a decreasing apex turn.  All the fancy terminology aside, there was a hill which had a turn at the bottom of it, I popped over the top of the hill going about 43 (incoming speed for my turn) lined myself up properly, swerved around a patch of gravel, hit my turn, rolled on the throttle, saw a patch a gravel, had my rear tire swing out from under me, slide off the road into the soft dirt shoulder and then my front wheel followed.  Well, I went from a 45 degree turn to a straight up in .5 of a second and flew over the bike, pushed off so it wouldn't highside me and I slid into the road.  The bike slid into the ditch where it shattered my fairings (right side if I remember right) and my instrument cluster.  My front forks are slightly bent.  So now it's 1 AM and alls I really want is a cute girl to cuddle with, a whiskey and coke to relax me, and someone to tell me everything will be alright.  I mean I know it will be and shit'll buff out but this is just one thing added to the mix...  More straw onto the camel's back, let's see how much more he holds before it breaks.  Definitely not looking to have another breakdown this year, 3 months of depression last year was bad enough.  But it could have been worse, my pants didn't get torn up but my legs got slightly scratched, my hands are ok minus a slight weird thing on my left hand, and my left lower leg is hurting like a mother. rest of me is fine.  Alls I ask for is a girl to cuddle with and a drink and I get neither... blah, sometimes my life just depresses me.  That or I'm too picky, but I like being picky.  Only few girls I would actually date or consider worth my time.
